parameters: Clea: I'm tired of being bombarded with questions...

Clea: The hero who saves the country, the Dragon Slayer...
Even if you suddenly say something like that... What should
I do?

Clea: I fought for myself, for my own sake... I'm definitely
not a hero.
Court Magician Eratoma: I apologize, did I disturb you?

Clea: No, I'm the one who should apologize for speaking out
of turn.

Court Magician Eratoma: It's fine, it's fine! This vast sky
doesn't belong to anyone!

Court Magician Eratoma: It exists equally for the wealthy,
the poor, the royal family, the slaves, and everyone else.
Court Magician Eratoma: So, how was the dragon?
Clea: Huh, yes, it was quite a formidable enemy.

Clea: It's almost like a miracle that I was able to defeat
it. Even if I'm told to fight again, I don't think I can do
it.

Court Magician Eratoma: I see, I see...! What did the dragon
look like?

Clea: It was in a pretty decayed state. If it had been in
its complete form... I don't want to think about it.

Court Magician Eratoma: You have a wonderful observation! A
warrior who firmly focuses on the enemy in front of them!

Court Magician Eratoma: Those eyes are the same as those of
a magician who gazes at the truth! I am Court Magician
Eratoma, pleased to make your acquaintance.
Clea: Actually, we have met once before.

Court Magician Eratoma: I apologize for that! Ahaha, I won't
forget, I absolutely won't forget.
Court Magician Eratoma: Then, let's meet again!

Clea (With eyes that seem to see through to the depths of
one's heart, so cold-hearted...)
Clea (It feels like her eyes resemble those of a dragon)
Thief Nora: Clea-san, you were here!

Thief Nora: I'm glad you're here! I thought you had gone
ahead.

Court Magician Relm: You were quite interested in this
genius magician, huh! Well, it was mostly just humans who
couldn't understand my story!

Sister Eleo: Thanks to your speech, the party ended early
and that's a good thing.

Sister Eleo: ...It would have been nice if Sophia-san had
come too.
